#### Login-keyring Management Guide (Cinnamon/Linux Mint)

##### SEO
Stop "Unlock login keyring" in Linux Mint.

##### Overview
- Login-keyring password SHOULD match user login password if user logs in manually
- Login-keyring password SHOULD be empty if "login automatically" IS used

###### For Manual Login Users:
- Open "Passwords and Keys"
- Right-click Login keyring
- Select "Change Password"
- Set to match user login password

###### For Auto-Login Users:
- Open "Passwords and Keys"
- Right-click Login keyring
- Select "Change Password"
- Leave password fields empty
- Acknowledge security warning

###### Alternative:
- Configure applications to not use keyring (if supported)
- Example: Chrome has this option

Note: Empty keyring password reduces security but eliminates unlock prompts.
